Part 1 ‚Äì Introduction, Architecture, Core Concepts, and Foundations
CHAPTER 1 ‚Äì What is SharePoint? (Complete Explanation)
SharePoint is Microsoft‚Äôs platform used for:
Document Management
Intranet Sites
Team collaboration
Business automation
Secure file storage
Content sharing
Workflow solutions
Enterprise search
Integration with Microsoft 365 (Teams, OneDrive, PowerApps, Power Automate)

Where SharePoint is used?
Business Need	How SharePoint Helps
Document storage	Libraries, versioning, metadata
Sharing & collaboration	Real-time co-authoring
Secure information	Permissions, policies
Automation	Power Automate Workflows
Websites/Intranets	Modern/Classic sites
Knowledge management	Pages, hubs, search center
Integration	M365, Teams, Power Platform

CHAPTER 2 ‚Äì Evolution of SharePoint (History)
1990s-Started as a web-based document management system.
2001 ‚Äì SharePoint Portal Server. First official release.
2007 ‚Äì SharePoint MOSS. Big jump with workflows, metadata, enterprise search.
2010 ‚Äì SharePoint Server 2010. Sandbox solutions, BCS, improved UI.
2013 ‚Äì SharePoint Server 2013. Modern apps, cloud-first direction.
2016 ‚Äì Hybrid SharePoint. Integration with Microsoft 365.
2019 ‚Äì Last On-Prem Modern Version. Modern UI, hybrid support.

SharePoint Online ‚Äì Continuous Updates
Cloud-based, auto-updated, part of Microsoft 365.

CHAPTER 3 ‚Äì SharePoint Online Architecture (Complete Breakdown)
SharePoint Online is built on Multi-tenant cloud architecture.
Layers of Architecture:
1. Tenant Level
Your Microsoft 365 subscription
Contains all SharePoint sites
Managed by Global Admin & SharePoint Admin

2. Site Collections (Sites)
Every team site/communication site is a site collection.
Root site (https://tenant.sharepoint.com/)

3. Sites & Subsites
Modern approach: avoid subsites, use independent sites connected via Hub sites.

4. Lists & Libraries
Stores structured information
Document libraries: files
Lists: data tables (similar to Excel)

5. Pages
Content pages built with web parts

6. Web Parts
UI building blocks: Hero, List, Document Library, Embed, Image, etc.

7. Storage
Comes from OneDrive + SharePoint pooled storage
Auto-expanding storage in Microsoft 365 plans

CHAPTER 4 ‚Äì Types of SharePoint Sites
1Ô∏è‚É£ Team Site
