ADVANCED ADMINISTRATION, SECURITY, COMPLIANCE & GOVERNANCE

üß© CHAPTER 16 ‚Äì SharePoint Admin Center (Modern Admin Center)

The SharePoint Admin Center is the central place for all SharePoint & OneDrive management inside Microsoft 365.

16.1 What You Can Manage in Admin Center

The modern admin center provides:

‚úî Site Management

Create new sites (Team sites, Communication sites)

View all sites in the tenant

Edit site owners, storage limits, external sharing, templates

Delete/restore sites

Change primary administrator

Configure Hub site settings


‚úî Policies

Sharing policies

Access control

Idle session sign-out

Network and location restrictions


‚úî Content Services

Term Store (managed metadata)

Content Type Gallery

Migration Manager

Record Management settings


‚úî OneDrive Admin Controls

Sync client settings

Default storage limits

User account access after employee leaves

Sharing and security settings



---

üß© CHAPTER 17 ‚Äì SITE MANAGEMENT IN DETAIL


---

17.1 Site Creation Types

SharePoint supports:

1. Team Site

Connected to a Microsoft 365 group

Used for collaboration

Integrated with Planner, Outlook, Teams

Has shared mailbox + calendar


2. Communication Site

Not connected to a group

Broadcast information to large audiences

Used for portals, intranets, dashboards


3. Classic Sites (Deprecated)

Used only for legacy apps

Should not be used for new solutions



---

17.2 Site Settings You Can Configure

‚úî Site Name & URL

‚úî Site Template (Modern only)

‚úî Site Owners

‚úî Storage Quota

‚úî Sharing Level

Anyone with link

New and existing guests

Only existing guests

Only internal users


‚úî Sensitivity Labels

Control classification:

Public

Confidential

Highly Confidential


‚úî Delete or Restore Site

Deleted sites go to Site Recycle Bin (93 days retention)



---

üß© CHAPTER 18 ‚Äì MANAGED METADATA & TERM STORE


---

18.1 What is Managed Metadata?

A centralized way to store classification labels used across the tenant.

You can create:

Term Groups

Term Sets

Terms

Custom properties

Localization for multiple languages



---

18.2 Why Use Managed Metadata?

Consistency across libraries

Reusable tags

Better search ranking

Navigation building



---

18.3 Applications

Enterprise Keywords

Content Type tagging

Navigation menus

Search refiners



