üß© CHAPTER 20 ‚Äì SHAREPOINT SECURITY MODEL


---

20.1 Authentication vs Authorization

Authentication ‚Üí Who you are

Authorization ‚Üí What you can access


Modern SharePoint uses:

Azure AD Authentication

Conditional Access Policies

MFA



---

20.2 Permission Levels

Built-in permission levels:

Level	Description

Full Control	All permissions
Edit	Add/edit/delete lists
Contribute	Add, edit, delete items
Read	Read-only
View Only	View-only for Web Pages



---

20.3 SharePoint Groups

Owners (full control)

Members (edit)

Visitors (read)


Custom groups can also be created.


---

20.4 Sharing Controls

Admin can configure:

External sharing ON/OFF

User-link expiration

Domain allow/block lists

Anonymous links



---

üß© CHAPTER 21 ‚Äì COMPLIANCE, RETENTION & RECORDS MANAGEMENT


---

21.1 Microsoft Purview Compliance Integration

SharePoint integrates with Purview for:

‚úî Data Loss Prevention (DLP)

Blocks sensitive data like:

PAN

Aadhaar

Passport

Financial information

Health data


‚úî Sensitivity Labels

Automatic classification of documents.

‚úî Retention Policies

Keep content for X years

Auto-delete content after retention

Retain-only (cannot delete manually)



---

21.2 Records Management

Documents can be declared as records:

Cannot delete

Cannot modify

Can track auditing



---

üß© CHAPTER 22 ‚Äì ONE DRIVE ADMINISTRATION


---

22.1 OneDrive Default Storage

Default: 1 TB

Can increase up to 5 TB per user



---

22.2 OneDrive Sharing Policies

Control external sharing

Block downloading

Block shared folder syncing



---

22.3 Sync Controls

Allow/block syncing on unmanaged devices

Limit syncing to specific domains

Control bandwidth usage



---

22.4 Access After Employee Leaves

Admin can configure:

Keep files for 30 days (default)

Transfer ownership

Disable access immediately



