PART 5

‚≠ê SPFx DEVELOPMENT (BEGINNER ‚Üí ADVANCED)

üß© CHAPTER 29 ‚Äì What is SPFx?

The SharePoint Framework (SPFx) is a client-side development model used to build:

‚úî Web Parts
‚úî Extensions
‚úî Custom Forms
‚úî Command Sets
‚úî Application Customizers
‚úî Full React apps in SharePoint

Key Features

100% client-side

Runs in modern SharePoint pages

Supports React, Angular, Vue, jQuery, plain JS

Uses TypeScript + Node.js + Webpack

Integrates with Microsoft Graph

Supports Teams apps

Works with On-Prem (SP 2016, 2019) and Online



---

üß© CHAPTER 30 ‚Äì SPFx Architecture

SPFx runs directly in the browser.
It is built using:

Node.js ‚Äì runtime

Yeoman ‚Äì scaffolding

Gulp ‚Äì task runner

Webpack ‚Äì bundling

TypeScript ‚Äì scripting

React ‚Äì UI framework (recommended)


Architecture Layers

+-------------------------------+
|      SharePoint Page         |
+-------------------------------+
|     SPFx Framework APIs      |
+-------------------------------+
|     Your Web Part Code       |
+-------------------------------+
|     TypeScript + React       |
+-------------------------------+
| Node.js + Gulp + Webpack     |
+-------------------------------+

SPFx renders components inside a SharePoint Canvas.


---

üß© CHAPTER 31 ‚Äì Environment Setup

Install the necessary tools:

‚úî 1. Install Node.js

Supported versions change often‚Äîuse Microsoft recommended LTS.

https://nodejs.org/

‚úî 2. Install Yeoman & SPFx Generator

npm install -g yo gulp
npm install -g @microsoft/generator-sharepoint

‚úî 3. Install Visual Studio Code

IDE for SPFx.

‚úî 4. Install Git

For version control.

‚úî 5. Install PnPjs Library (optional but recommended)

npm install @pnp/sp @pnp/graph


---

üß© CHAPTER 32 ‚Äì Create Your First SPFx Web Part

Use Yeoman to create a new project:

yo @microsoft/sharepoint

You will be asked:

‚úî Solution name

‚úî Target environment

SharePoint Online (recommended)

Teams

SP 2019

SP 2016


‚úî WebPart type

Web Part

Extension


‚úî Template

React

No JavaScript

Knockout


Choose React.


---

Directory structure

src/
  webparts/
    yourWebPart/
      components/
      YourWebPart.ts
config/
node_modules/
gulpfile.js
package.json


---

üß© CHAPTER 33 ‚Äì Run SPFx Locally

Use the SharePoint Workbench:

gulp serve

Opens:

https://localhost:4321/temp/workbench.html

OR Online:

https://<tenant>.sharepoint.com/_layouts/15/workbench.aspx


---

üß© CHAPTER 34 ‚Äì Deploy SPFx Web Part to SharePoint

Step 1 ‚Üí Build

gulp build
gulp bundle --ship

Step 2 ‚Üí Package

gulp package-solution --ship

Creates:

sharepoint/solution/*.sppkg

Step 3 ‚Üí Upload to App Catalog

SharePoint Admin Center ‚Üí More Features ‚Üí App Catalog

Step 4 ‚Üí Add App to Site

Site Contents ‚Üí Add App ‚Üí Your SPFx App

Now the web part is available in the ‚Äú+ Add Web Part‚Äù panel.


---

üß© CHAPTER 35 ‚Äì SPFx WEB PART DEVELOPMENT (ADVANCED)


---

‚úî Using React inside SPFx

React component rendering happens in:

YourWebPart.ts ‚Üí ReactDOM.render()

Component folder:

components/MyComponent.tsx

Sample React Component:

export default function MyComponent(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Hello {props.name}</h1>
    </div>
  );
}


---

‚úî Using State

const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0);


---

‚úî Using Props

<MyComponent name="SharePoint" />


---

‚úî Using Services (PnPjs)

import { sp } from '@pnp/sp';

sp.web.lists.getByTitle("Demo").items.get().then(items => {
  console.log(items);
});


---

üß© CHAPTER 36 ‚Äì EXTENSIONS

