yo @microsoft/sharepoint
‚Üí Extension ‚Üí Application Customizer


---

‚úî Field Customizers

Modify how list fields look.

Example:

Status badges

Rating stars



---

‚úî Command Set

Add buttons to list toolbar.

Example:

Approve

Reject

Custom workflow


Generate:

yo @microsoft/sharepoint
‚Üí Extension ‚Üí ListView Command Set


---

üß© CHAPTER 37 ‚Äì API INTEGRATION


---

‚úî Microsoft Graph API

Install Graph:

npm install @microsoft/mgt @microsoft/mgt-react

OR PnP Graph:

npm install @pnp/graph

Get user data:

graph.me.get().then(user => {
  console.log(user.displayName);
});


---

‚úî Calling External API

Use AadHttpClient:

this.context.aadHttpClientFactory
  .getClient(appId)
  .then(client => {
    return client.get(apiURL, HttpClient.configurations.v1);
  })


---

‚úî Calling SharePoint REST API

this.context.spHttpClient.get(
  "/_api/web/lists/getByTitle('Demo')/items",
  SPHttpClient.configurations.v1
);


---

üß© CHAPTER 38 ‚Äì DEPLOYMENT MODELS

‚úî 1. Tenant Wide Deployment

Web part available on all sites.

‚úî 2. Site App Catalog

App added only to specific site.

‚úî 3. Teams Deployment

Enable manifest ‚Üí Teams App.


---

üß© CHAPTER 39 ‚Äì PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION

‚úî Lazy Loading

Load components only when needed.

‚úî Code Splitting

Use React lazy.

‚úî Caching with PnPjs

sp.web.lists.usingCaching().get();

‚úî Minification

Bundling with Webpack reduces size.


---

üß© CHAPTER 40 ‚Äì BEST PRACTICES FOR SPFx

‚úî Use React and PnPjs

FASTEST and MOST PRODUCTIVE.

‚úî Avoid Large Bundles

Use libraries wisely.

‚úî Use Environment Variables

Store API URLs safely.

‚úî Use Graph API for user info

‚úî Keep UI responsive

Using Fluent UI or custom components.


---

