---

üß© CHAPTER 45 ‚Äì SHAREPOINT REST API (Modern)

Modern, fast, used everywhere.

REST URL format:

https://<tenant>.sharepoint.com/sites/<site>/_api/<service>


---

‚úî 45.1 Authentication

Uses OAuth tokens automatically in:

SPFx

Power Automate

PowerApps


For external apps:

Azure AD App Registration

Client Credentials flow



---

‚úî 45.2 GET All Lists

/_api/web/lists


---

‚úî 45.3 GET Specific List

/_api/web/lists/getByTitle('Employees')


---

‚úî 45.4 GET Items

/_api/web/lists/getByTitle('Employees')/items


---

‚úî 45.5 GET Item by ID

/items(5)


---

‚úî 45.6 Filter Items

/items?$filter=Department eq 'HR'


---

‚úî 45.7 Select Specific Columns

/items?$select=Id,Title,Location


---

‚úî 45.8 Expand Lookup Columns

/items?$expand=Manager


---

‚úî 45.9 TOP Items

/items?$top=50


---

‚úî 45.10 Add Item (POST)

{
 "__metadata": { "type": "SP.Data.EmployeesListItem" },
 "Title": "John",
 "Department": "Finance"
}


---

‚úî 45.11 Update Item (MERGE)

Send headers:

X-HTTP-Method: MERGE
IF-MATCH: *


---

‚úî 45.12 Delete Item

POST with:
X-HTTP-Method: DELETE
IF-MATCH: *


---


---

üß© CHAPTER 46 ‚Äì CSOM (Client-Side Object Model)

Used in C#, PowerShell, Azure Functions.


---

‚úî 46.1 Authentication Example in C#

var context = new ClientContext("https://tenant/sites/site");
context.Credentials = new SharePointOnlineCredentials(user, securePassword);


---

‚úî 46.2 Get Web Title

var web = context.Web;
context.Load(web);
context.ExecuteQuery();
Console.WriteLine(web.Title);


---

‚úî 46.3 Get Lists

var lists = context.Web.Lists;
context.Load(lists);
context.ExecuteQuery();


---

‚úî 46.4 Create List Item

var list = context.Web.Lists.GetByTitle("Employees");
var item = list.AddItem(new ListItemCreationInformation());
item["Title"] = "John";
item.Update();
context.ExecuteQuery();


---

‚úî 46.5 Update / Delete is similar

CSOM is very reliable and most used in automation.


---


---

üß© CHAPTER 47 ‚Äì JSOM (Legacy JavaScript Object Model)

Used only in classic SharePoint.

Not recommended anymore, but you should know it.


---

‚úî JSOM Example

var ctx = SP.ClientContext.get_current();
var web = ctx.get_web();
ctx.load(web);
ctx.executeQueryAsync(() => {
  console.log(web.get_title());
});


---


---

üß© CHAPTER 48 ‚Äì MICROSOFT GRAPH FOR SHAREPOINT

Graph accesses SharePoint through OneDrive endpoints.


---

‚úî 48.1 Get Drive of a Site

/v1.0/sites/{site-id}/drive


---

‚úî 48.2 Get Items in Document Library

/v1.0/sites/{site-id}/drive/root/children


---

‚úî 48.3 Upload File

PUT /drive/items/root:/Folder1/test.txt:/content


---

‚úî 48.4 Get User Information

/v1.0/me


---

‚úî 48.5 List Members of a Group

/v1.0/groups/{id}/members


---

When to Use Graph Instead of REST?

Use Graph when accessing:

Users

Groups

Teams

OneDrive files

App permissions



---


---

üß© CHAPTER 49 ‚Äì PnPJS (Modern JavaScript SDK)

The BEST library to use with SPFx + React.


---

‚úî 49.1 Setup

npm install @pnp/sp @pnp/graph

Init:

sp.setup({ spfxContext: this.context });


---

‚úî 49.2 Get Items

sp.web.lists.getByTitle("Employees").items.get()


---

‚úî 49.3 Add Item

sp.web.lists.getByTitle("Employees").items.add({
  Title: "John"
});


---

‚úî 49.4 Update Item

sp.web.lists.getByTitle("Employees").items.getById(5).update({
  Department: "IT"
});


---

‚úî 49.5 Delete Item

sp.web.lists.getByTitle("Employees").items.getById(5).delete();


---

‚úî 49.6 File Upload

sp.web.getFolderByServerRelativeUrl("/sites/demo/Docs")
  .files.add("test.txt", "Hello", true);


---


---

üß© CHAPTER 50 ‚Äì PnP POWERSHELL

Most powerful automation tool.


---

‚úî 50.1 Install

Install-Module PnP.PowerShell


---

‚úî 50.2 Connect

Connect-PnPOnline -Url "https://tenant.sharepoint.com" -Interactive


---

‚úî 50.3 Get Sites

Get-PnPTenantSite


---

‚úî 50.4 Create List Item

Add-PnPListItem -List "Employees" -Values @{
  Title="John"; Department="Finance"
}


---

‚úî 50.5 Upload File

Add-PnPFile -Path "C:\Docs\file.pdf" -Folder "Shared Documents"


---

‚úî 50.6 Apply Site Template

Invoke-PnPSiteTemplate -Path template.xml


---

PnP PowerShell is SUPER EXTENSIVE‚Äîyour admin automation works here.


---


---

üß© CHAPTER 51 ‚Äì SHAREPOINT SEARCH API

Allows building custom search pages.


---

‚úî 51.1 Basic Search

/_api/search/query?queryText='report'


---

‚úî 51.2 Search with Filters

queryText='Title:Invoice'


---

‚úî 51.3 Search With Refiners

refiners=Department


---

‚úî 51.4 Get Search Suggestions

/_api/search/suggest?queryText='sal'


---

Search API is essential for enterprise search solutions.


