8.11 Permissions & Access Management (MOST IMPORTANT)

Default Permission Levels:

Permission	Description

Full Control	Admin
Edit	Add/edit/delete items
Contribute	Add/edit items
Read	View only
Limited Access	Required for hierarchy


Permission Hierarchy:

1. Site Collection Admin
2. Site Owner
3. Members (Edit)
4. Visitors (Read)



SharePoint Groups:
Owners
Members
Visitors
Custom groups


Permission Best Practices:

‚úî Use groups, not individuals
‚úî Break inheritance only when needed
‚úî Avoid giving Edit to everyone
‚úî Use ‚ÄúAccess Request‚Äù feature
‚úî Use ‚ÄúShare‚Äù carefully
‚úî Apply labels or DLP for confidential docs

