Cards	Visibility, default value, rules
Validation	Required, mandatory rules
Conditional logic	Show/hide based on user
Patch for save	Full control

9.5 PowerApps Delegation with SharePoint

Delegation = Large data handling.

SharePoint delegation supported for:

Filter

Sort

LookUp

Search

StartsWith

= / < / > / <= / >=


Not supported:

Contains

CountIf

ForAll with conditions


Avoid delegation warnings by using:

StartsWith instead of Search/Contains

Filter instead of ForAll

Indexing columns

9.6 PowerApps Forms + SharePoint Columns

Column types best for PowerApps:

SharePoint Column	PowerApps Behavior

Single line text	Text input
Choice	Dropdown/ComboBox
Lookup	ComboBox
Person	People picker
Yes/No	Toggle
Date	Date Picker
Hyperlink	Text input
Attachments	Attach control


Columns NOT recommended:

‚ùå Multiple lines rich text
‚ùå Lookup with more than 12 columns
‚ùå Managed metadata (limited support)


---

9.7 Patch Function (MOST Important Advanced Concept)

Patch is used to:

Create items

Update items

Partial updates

Update related lists


Example:

Patch(
    'Requests',
    Defaults('Requests'),
    {
        Title: txtTitle.Text,
        Status: "Pending",
        Requestor: User().FullName
    }
)


---

