‚úÖ PART 10 ‚Äî SHAREPOINT INTERVIEW QUESTIONS

10.1 Beginner / Basic Questions

Q1. What is SharePoint?

Answer: SharePoint is a web-based collaboration platform from Microsoft. It allows storing, organizing, sharing, and accessing information from any device.

Q2. Difference between SharePoint Online and On-Premises?

Online: Cloud-based, subscription, always updated

On-Premises: Installed on local servers, more control, requires updates


Q3. What are SharePoint sites?

Team Site: Collaboration

Communication Site: Broadcast information

Hub Site: Connects multiple sites


Q4. What is a SharePoint List?

A list is a collection of items with structured columns (like a database table).

Q5. What is a Document Library?

A library is a list designed to store documents and their versions.

Q6. Explain Versioning in SharePoint

Major versions: 1.0, 2.0

Minor versions: 1.1, 1.2

Helps track changes and restore files


Q7. What is a Content Type?

A reusable set of columns, templates, and workflows used across lists/libraries.

Q8. What is Managed Metadata?

Hierarchical taxonomy for consistent metadata across SharePoint using term sets.

Q9. What are SharePoint Groups?

Collections of users with assigned permission levels (Owners, Members, Visitors).

Q10. Difference between Permissions & Groups

Permission: Access level (Read, Edit, Full Control)

Group: Collection of users with assigned permissions

10.2 Intermediate Questions

Q11. What is a Hub Site?

Connects multiple sites for unified navigation, branding, and search.

Q12. What is a Site Collection?

A container for multiple sites with a common top-level site, permissions, and settings.

Q13. Explain Recycle Bin in SharePoint Online

First stage: 93 days (user can restore)

Second stage: Additional 93 days (admin can restore)


Q14. What are SharePoint Lists Views?

Custom representations of list items using filters, sorting, grouping, or formatting.

Q15. What is JSON Column Formatting?

Customizes the UI of SharePoint columns using JSON, e.g., colors, icons, badges.

Q16. What is SPFx?

SharePoint Framework (SPFx) is the modern client-side development model for SharePoint Online.

Q17. Difference between Classic and Modern Pages

Classic: Legacy, supports server-side code

Modern: Mobile-friendly, responsive, client-side code, SPFx


Q18. Explain Lookup Columns

Connect a list to another list‚Äôs column values to avoid duplication.

Q19. What is a SharePoint Workflow?

Automated sequence of actions triggered by an event, e.g., approval, notification.

Q20. What is Power Automate integration?

Use Power Automate to trigger workflows based on SharePoint events (item created, modified, deleted).

10.3 Advanced Questions

Q21. Explain SharePoint REST API

REST endpoints to access SharePoint lists, libraries, sites, users, and more via HTTP.

Q22. Difference between CSOM, JSOM, REST

Model	Language	Usage	Notes

CSOM	C# / .NET	Client apps	Rich object model
JSOM	JavaScript	Web pages	Legacy, classic pages
REST	HTTP/JSON	Web & SPFx	Modern, cross-platform


Q23. What is Microsoft Graph API for SharePoint?

Unified API to access M365 services (SharePoint, OneDrive, Teams, Users).

Q24. What is PnP PowerShell?

PnP PowerShell is an extension module for advanced automation and management of SharePoint Online.

Q25. What is a Webhook in SharePoint?

Allows external systems to receive notifications when list items are added, modified, or deleted.

Q26. Explain Term Store & Managed Metadata

Term Store: Central hub for metadata

Managed Metadata: Standardized metadata used across sites


Q27. How to optimize PowerApps connected to SharePoint

Use delegable functions

Use collections for repeated data

Avoid nested galleries

Index columns


Q28. Explain Hub Site vs Team Site vs Communication Site

Team Site ‚Üí Collaboration

Communication Site ‚Üí Broadcast info

Hub Site ‚Üí Connect multiple sites


Q29. Explain Site Design & Site Script

Site Design: Predefined configuration of site (lists, theme, nav)

Site Script: JSON file defining actions to apply in Site Design


Q30. How do you apply Retention Policies in SharePoint?

Tenant-wide or per-site retention

Can auto-delete or preserve items

Can apply labels for compliance



---

