PART 12 ‚Äî SharePoint Advanced Concepts & Enterprise Features

12.1 SharePoint Security & Permissions

1. Permission Levels
Full Control: All permissions
Design: Can edit pages, lists, and libraries
Edit: Add, edit, delete items
Contribute: Add/edit items only
Read: View items

2. SharePoint Groups
Owner, Member, Visitor groups
Assign permission levels to groups, not individual users

3. Unique Permissions
Break inheritance on lists, libraries, or items
Apply item-level security

4. External Sharing
Share links: Anyone, People in organization, Specific people
Expiration and password protection for links
Domain restrictions

5. Sensitivity Labels
Classify and protect content
Restrict sharing, apply encryption, monitor access

12.2 SharePoint Search

1. Modern Search
Enterprise search across sites, libraries, lists
Refiners and filters for precise results

2. Search Schema
Managed properties
Crawled properties
Mapping to metadata

3. Search Center
Centralized search experience
Custom search results pages

4. Query Rules
Promote results for specific keywords
Add result blocks, recommendations

5. Search Web Parts
Highlighted content, People search, File viewer

12.3 SharePoint Content Management

1. Document Management
Versioning (major/minor)
Check-in/check-out
Metadata navigation

2. Records Management
Content types for structured record keeping
Retention labels & policies

3. Content Organizer
Rules-based routing to libraries/folders
Auto-classification based on metadata

4. Managed Metadata & Term Store
Centralized taxonomy for enterprise-wide consistency
Hierarchical term sets
Used in navigation, filtering, and metadata columns

12.4 Compliance & Governance
1. Retention Policies
Automatically keep/delete content
Applied to sites, libraries, or content types

2. Audit Logs
Track access, edits, downloads, and deletion
Useful for compliance and security

3. Data Loss Prevention (DLP)
Policies to prevent sharing sensitive content externally
Can block, warn, or log actions

4. Governance Plan
Naming conventions for sites and libraries
Permission management
Archiving and site lifecycle policies

12.5 Enterprise Integration

1. SharePoint + Teams
Team sites connected to Teams channels
